<TITLE> Another extremist killed in shootout with police in Kushtia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)  After a few days' break, another alleged top militant Mojibar Rahman Babu (40) was killed in a gun battle with police early on Friday in Mirpur, Kushtia. Mirpur police chief Sheikh Anwar Hossain said Babu, a regional leader of Gano Mukti Fouj, was killed at Swarupdaha village under Mirpur Upazila. "Tipped off about a clandestine rendezvous of extremist elements to be held near a culvert on Swarupdaha-Koimari road, police raided the spot. The terrorists opened fire triggering a shootout with police," said the police chief. Mojibar was eventually bullet-hit and killed in the shootout, he said. Police recovered a firearm and five rounds of ammunition from the scene. Mojibar faced six cases filed against him with Mirpur police station. His body was taken to the Kushtia sadar hospital morgue for autopsy. bdnews2
